# Some informations
print('- The format of predictions.render() is: ', np.array(predictions.render()).shape)
print('- What we need is just: ', np.array(predictions.render()).shape[1:4])
print('- So we can use a np.function called "squeeze" to obtain: ', np.squeeze(predictions.render()).shape)
print('- This is why we use: plt.imshow(np.squeeze(predictions.render()))')

plt.figure(figsize=(10,8))
plt.imshow(np.squeeze(predictions.render()))
plt.axis('off');

- The format of predictions.render() is:  (1, 3456, 5184, 3)
- What we need is just:  (3456, 5184, 3)
- So we can use a np.function called "squeeze" to obtain:  (3456, 5184, 3)
- This is why we use: plt.imshow(np.squeeze(predictions.render()))

3. Detection on an video¶

3.1. Video from webcam¶

In [ ]:
# Define the time between two consecutive frames
waiting_time = 1

# Open the webcam
cap = cv2.VideoCapture(0)

while cap.isOpened():

    # Capture frame, if all went good then 'ret==True'
    ret, frame = cap.read()

    # If all went good, namely we have a frame:
    if ret == True:

        # Make predictions
        predictions = model(frame)

        # Plot predictions
        cv2.imshow('YOLOv5 predictions on WebCam', np.squeeze(predictions.render()))

        # If we press the exit-buttom 'q' we end the webcam caption
        if cv2.waitKey(waiting_time) & 0xFF == ord('q'):
            break

    # If something went bad, namely we did not get correctly the frame we exit all
    else:
        break

# Close everything in the end
cap.release()
cv2.destroyAllWindows()

3.2. Video.mp4¶

In [ ]:
waiting_time = 1

# Open the video
cap = cv2.VideoCapture('./Miscellaneous/cars.mp4')

while cap.isOpened():
    ret, frame = cap.read()
    if ret == True:
        predictions = model(frame)
        cv2.imshow('YOLOv5 predictions on WebCam', np.squeeze(predictions.render()))
        if cv2.waitKey(waiting_time) & 0xFF == ord('q'):
            break
    else:
        break

cap.release()
cv2.destroyAllWindows()
